PRESIDENT John Magufuli has appointed Mr Albinus Mgonya a District Commissioner (DC) for Mvomero in Morogoro Region. Prior to his appointment, Mr Mgonya was the Assistant Regional Administrative Secretary in Rukwa. He is replacing Mr Mohammed Utaly. According to a statement issued by the Director of Presidential Communications Mr Gerson Msigwa yesterday, the President also appointed Mr Waziri Kombo, the District Executive Director (DED) for Biharamulo, Kagera region. Mr Kombo, who prior to his appointment was the administrative officer in Morogoro municipal council, is taking over from Ms Wendi Ng'ahala. The appointees are supposed to report at the State House Chamwino in Dodoma region today, read part of the statement.